# 1) All nitrogens are treated only as proton donors. Their acceptor
# valencies are consistently set to 0.
# 
# 2) For His, the charges on ND1 and NE2 could be +1 or 0 (depending
# on the pH). But I indicated these atoms as having a single + charge to
# account for an optimistic hydrogen bonding scenario.
# 
# 3) In all cases where there is a charge resonance (eg. OD1/OD2 of ASP), I
# have given both atoms a unit charge.
#
# 4) various amides NH seem to be an acceptor too (according to statistics,
#    partly because they may be mislabeled in structures, ie N, Q sidechains)
#
#                                Donor Acceptor 
#                                  Valencies      Charge
#
ATMGRP 'N'                            1       1       0
  ATOM            '*'       'N'
ATMGRP  'O'                           0       2       0
  ATOM            '*'       'O'
ATMGRP  'SG'                          1       0       0
  ATOM            'CYS'     'SG'
ATMGRP  'OD1/2'                       0       2       -0.5
  ATOM            'ASP'     'OD1'
  ATOM            'ASP'     'OD2'
ATMGRP  'OE1/2'                       0       2       -0.5
  ATOM            'GLU'     'OE1'
  ATOM            'GLU'     'OE2'
ATMGRP  'ND1'                         1       0        0
  ATOM            'HSD'     'ND1'
ATMGRP  'NE2'                         1       0        0
  ATOM            'HSD'     'NE2'
ATMGRP  'NZ'                          3       0       +1
  ATOM            'LYS'     'NZ'
ATMGRP  'SD'                          0       0       0
  ATOM            'MET'     'SD'
ATMGRP  'OD1'                         0       2       0
  ATOM            'ASN'     'OD1'
ATMGRP  'ND2'                         2       1       0
  ATOM            'ASN'     'ND2'
ATMGRP  'OE1'                         0       2       0
  ATOM            'GLN'     'OE1'
ATMGRP  'NE2'                         2       1       0
  ATOM            'GLN'     'NE2'
ATMGRP  'NE'                          1       0       0
  ATOM            'ARG'     'NE'
ATMGRP  'NH1/2'                       2       0       +0.5
  ATOM            'ARG'     'NH1'
  ATOM            'ARG'     'NH2'
ATMGRP  'OG'                          1       2       0
  ATOM            'SER'     'OG'
ATMGRP  'OG1'                         1       2       0
  ATOM            'THR'     'OG1'
ATMGRP  'NE1'                         1       0       0
  ATOM            'TRP'     'NE1'
ATMGRP  'OH'                          1       0       0
  ATOM            'TYR'     'OH'
ATMGRP  'SG2'                         0       0       0
  ATOM            'CSS'     'SG'
ATMGRP  'NH3'                         2       0       +1
  ATOM            '*'       'NH3'
ATMGRP  'OT1/2'                       0       2       -0.5
  ATOM            '*'       'OT1'
  ATOM            '*'       'OT2'
ATMGRP  '*:*'                         0       0       0
  ATOM            '*'       '*'
  ATOM            '*'       '*'
